## Instruction Hierarchy

When instructions conflict, the most specific source wins:

```
1. Agent-specific file (.opencode/agents/Name.md)   — highest priority
2. AGENTS.md                                         — project rules
3. _shared.md (this file)                            — shared context, lowest priority
```

If an agent file instruction contradicts `_shared.md` — follow the agent file.

## Language / i18n

Project supports multilingual agent output. Set `OPPENCODE_LANG` environment variable:

- `en` — English (default)
- `ru` — Russian (Русский)

Locale definitions in `.opencode/i18n/<locale>.yaml`. Agents read `OPPENCODE_LANG` and use the corresponding locale for status messages and user-facing output.

To add a new language:
1. Copy `.opencode/i18n/en.yaml` to `.opencode/i18n/<code>.yaml`
2. Translate all values
3. Set `OPPENCODE_LANG=<code>` to use it

